               <note type="abstract">Severus of Antioch was an Anti-Chalcedonian patriarch who wrote many treatises and homilies defending his community.  He attended meetings of Justinian to reconcile Chalceodnians and its opponents.  He also was the leader of a large group of Anti-Chalcedonian monks.  He wrote in Greek, but his works were preserved in Syriac.  </note>
